Reference: Xtrata — Positioning for Hackathons & Prize-Driven Events

Core Project Snapshot

Project Name: Xtrata
Tagline: A recursive on-chain memory layer for Bitcoin via Stacks

Xtrata is an on-chain memory layer for Bitcoin (via Stacks) designed to make media and app data permanent, reconstructable, and composable on-chain. Rather than stopping at pointer-to-metadata NFTs, Xtrata builds verifiable, modular on-chain data graphs using recursive relationships between inscriptions.

What Xtrata Solves
	•	Durable on-chain data: Payloads and media are stored and reconstructable without external off-chain dependencies.
	•	Deterministic reconstruction: Same bytes → same result — ideal for verifiable content.
	•	Recursion & composability: Parent-child inscription linkages create modular on-chain data structures.
	•	Ecosystem compatibility: SIP-009–compatible NFTs for broader tooling and marketplace support.
	•	Large media practicality: Chunked upload/read patterns allow scaling beyond small single-file NFTs.

Target Audiences / Stakeholders
	1.	Developers / Builders — infrastructure, data tooling, durable on-chain media.
	2.	Creators / Artists — permanent verifiable on-chain media and composable assets.
	3.	Collectors / Curators — provenance and reconstructability beyond pointers.
	4.	Integrators / Marketplaces — marketplaces, gallery tools, viewer interfaces.

